ABSTRACT

This project presents an automatic light control system using Arduino, PIR motion sensor, and Light Dependent Resistor (LDR). The system automatically turns the light ON when motion is detected in low light conditions and turns it OFF when sufficient light is available or no motion is detected. The main goal of this project is to reduce energy consumption and demonstrate a basic automation system using embedded technology.

INTRODUCTION

Automation systems play an important role in modern electrical and electronic applications. Manual control of lights often leads to unnecessary power wastage. An automatic light control system provides an efficient solution by ensuring that lights are only turned ON when required. This project focuses on designing a low-cost and simple automatic lighting system using Arduino, which can be used in homes, offices, corridors, and parking areas.

